  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 47 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1600 mg
servings: 2
---

Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{}ed water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @button mushrooms{8%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick pieces. (Skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!) Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Pat @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken or sausage and cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wash out pan.

> Use pan used for chicken or sausage here.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, melt @butter{2%tbsp} in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until just softened, ~{1%minute}. Add @flour{1%tablespoon} and cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Whisk in @milk{6.75%ounce} and ⅓ cup reserved pasta cooking water, breaking up any flour clumps. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} into pan with sauce until melted and combined. Stir in mushrooms, drained cavatappi, and @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Stir in chicken or sausage along with mushrooms.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} and scallion greens. Serve.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.